    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is great! We discussed in the team that we would like to fix as many of these issues as we can.\r\n\r\nWe want to add new static analysis to our build tooling for some of these issues. \r\n\r\nI think these are a few good places to start that wouldn't require a static analyzer. \r\n- [x] [unused code](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/SCC-U1000/occurrences) #6864\r\n- [x] [Using a deprecated function, variable, constant or field](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/SCC-SA1019/occurrences) (moved to #6891)\r\n- [x] ~~[File path traversal when extracting zip archive](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/GSC-G305/occurrences)~~ (offending code no longer exists)\r\n- [x] [The loop exits unconditionally after one iteration](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/SCC-SA4004/occurrences) #6906\r\n- [x] [Simplify make call by omitting redundant arguments](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/SCC-S1019/occurrences) #6949\r\n- [x] [Don’t use fmt.Sprintf(\"%s\", x) unnecessarily](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/SCC-S1025/occurrences) #6906\r\n- [x] And many of the anti-pattern suggestions would be welcome as well #6951\r\n\r\nI think these would be high value candidates for add a static analyzer in prysm.\r\n- [x] [Boolean expression has identical expressions on both sides](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/SCC-SA4000/occurrences) #7066\r\n- [x] ~~[Assigning to b.N in benchmarks detected](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/SCC-SA3001/occurrences)~~ (sometimes you really might want to assign a specific value, so an analyzer would be overkill here)\r\n- [x] [&*x gets simplified to x and it does not copy x](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/SCC-SA4001/occurrences) #7249\r\n- [x] [Shadow of builtin detected](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/CRT-A0001/occurrences) #7215\r\n- [x] [Slice can be used directly](https://deepsource.io/gh/chsatyap/prysm/issue/CRT-A0016/occurrences) #7321\r\n\r\nFor an example of a static analysis addition, please see #6401, #5403, #5296, #5456. ",
